ATTRIBUTION

This detection pack incorporates detection logic adapted from publicly
available work licensed under MIT and compatible terms. Specific attribution:

  - 3ch0p01nt/RedSun_Undefend (MIT) — RedSun and UnDefend primitive detection
    patterns. Original logic for several RS-T3-* and UD-T2-* rules.

  - jkerai1/KQL-Queries — REDSUN named pipe detection pattern
    (DesiredAccess + AcceptRemote signature).

  - microsoft/Microsoft-365-Defender-Hunting-Queries (MIT) — TVM table
    parsing patterns used in BH-T5-3.

Production hardening, Tier 0 / Tier 1 / Tier 4 rules, combined kill-chain
correlation, MITRE mapping, false-positive analysis, and the Defender XDR
vs Sentinel deployment split are original work.

Vulnerability research credit:
  - BlueHammer (CVE-2026-33825) — Zen Dodd and Yuanpei Xu (HUST / Diffract)
    via Microsoft, with corresponding public PoC by Chaotic Eclipse /
    Nightmare-Eclipse.
  - RedSun, UnDefend — Chaotic Eclipse / Nightmare-Eclipse.

Active exploitation reporting:
  - Huntress Labs — primary in-the-wild documentation.
